  "prompt": "What is an In-Flight Crew Member?",
  "response": "An **In-Flight Crew Member** is a professional responsible for ensuring the safety, comfort, and well-being of passengers during a flight. They work onboard aircraft as part of the cabin crew and are commonly referred to as flight attendants, cabin crew, or air stewards/stewardesses. Their primary duties include:\n\n1. **Safety Responsibilities**:\n   - Conducting pre-flight safety checks and briefings.\n   - Demonstrating the use of safety equipment (e.g., seat belts, oxygen masks, life vests).\n   - Ensuring passengers comply with safety regulations.\n   - Managing emergencies, such as medical situations or evacuations.\n\n2. **Customer Service**:\n   - Welcoming passengers and assisting with boarding.\n   - Serving meals, beverages, and snacks.\n   - Addressing passenger inquiries and providing information about the flight.\n   - Ensuring a comfortable and pleasant travel experience.\n\n3. **Operational Duties**:\n   - Preparing the cabin for takeoff and landing.\n   - Maintaining cleanliness and order in the cabin.\n   - Handling in-flight sales or duty-free items (if applicable).\n   - Communicating with the flight deck (pilots) as needed.\n\nIn-flight crew members undergo rigorous training in safety procedures, first aid, communication, and customer service to handle various situations effectively. Their role is crucial in ensuring a safe and enjoyable journey for all passengers.",
